  "raw_response": "\n\nVoici le call chain complet de `dispatch_webhook` :\n\n```\ndispatch_webhook(payload, user_id)          # apps/api/services/webhooks.py\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 _webhooks_admin_db()                    # apps/api/services/webhooks.py:8\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 supabase_admin()                    # apps/api/db.py:40\n\u2502   \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 DBSession(\"postgresql://localhost/tsbench?role=admin\")  # DB access\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 info(msg)                           # apps/api/utils/logging.py:12\n\u2502       \u2514\u2500\u2500 log(\"INFO\", msg)               # apps/api/utils/logging.py:5\n\u2502           \u2514\u2500\u2500 print(...)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 info(\"dispatch_webhook called by ...\")  # apps/api/utils/logging.py:12\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 log(\"INFO\", msg)                   # apps/api/utils/logging.py:5\n\u2502       \u2514\u2500\u2500 print(...)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 payload.get(\"check\", True)             # dict built-in\n```\n\n**Acc\u00e8s DB** : un seul, via `_webhooks_admin_db()` \u2192 `supabase_admin()` \u2192 `DBSession(...)` qui ouvre une session PostgreSQL privil\u00e9gi\u00e9e (r\u00f4le `admin`) sur `localhost/tsbench`.\n\n**R\u00e9sum\u00e9** : la fonction appelle 2 d\u00e9pendances directes (`_webhooks_admin_db`, `info`) et 3 indirectes (`supabase_admin`, `DBSession`, `log`). Le reste du corps est du code inerte (variables locales non utilis\u00e9es).",
